        jTextArea1.setText(" \nTraining and Placement Cell in the Institute plays a vital role and is becoming a key department of the Institute.Training & Placement Cell is devoted to \ncater to the needs of organizations in conducting campus interviews for placements. It is headed by a Professor designated as Training & Placement Officer \nin charge. The Cell is assisted by Student Placement Coordinators who lead a team of placement representatives from various courses of study. The Training & \nPlacement Cell ensures and takes care to provide the best arrangements and hospitality for the visiting companies' officials. As there are many more \nEngineering Colleges coming up , the competition for employment is increasing every day and the job of placement is becoming a challenging one. \n\nRole of Training & Placement Cell \n\n1) The Training & Placement Office of the Institute has the responsibility of facilitating the Campus Recruitment Programme for all disciplines. \n2) The Placement Office initiates and nurtures contacts with leading organizations for campus visits and is functional throughout the year. It endeavors to\n match the aspirations of the students with the needs of the Industry. It also assists the students for Summer/Winter Industrial training. \n3) The T&P Division also provides counseling and guidance to the students regarding the visiting organizations, selection procedure, preparation methods & \nresources thereby ensuring that the students are adequately equipped to face the recruitment tests. \n4) A team of Student Placement Coordinators duly assists the T&P Office. \n5) The auditorium, seminar halls and Interview cubicles, equipped with audio-visual aids provide the ideal venue for campus selection activities like \nPresentations, Written Test, Group Discussion and Interviews. \n6) The Placement Office ensures and takes care to provide the best arrangement and hospitality for officials of the visiting companies. \n\n\nActivities of Training and Placement Office \n\n1) Arranging inplant training for students \n2) Inviting various organizations for campus recruitment. \n3) Developing verbal and non-verbal communications \n4) Enhancing public speaking skills \n5) Imparting personality improvement through in-house and external expert faculty Programme \n6) Programs Providing Career planning and Career Mapping \n7) Administering aptitude tests \n8) Conducting group discussions and mock interview practice sessions \n9) Arranging on and off campus recruitments \n10) Personality development \n11) Interpersonal & Communication skills \n\n\nPlacement Procedure \n\n1) Invitations are sent to the Companies by the T&P office. \n2) To the responding companies, the details of the final year students opting for placement are sent as per their requirement. \n3) The companies have an option to go for the campus recruitment to the Constituent Colleges. \n4) The company is assigned a convenient date. \n5) After confirmation by the company, a pre-placement talk is arranged on the date. \n6) Once the intimation is received from the companies they are displayed on the T&P notice board so that the interested students may submit their names. \n7) The resumes of the students are then sent to the organization along with a tentative date for the campus interview (negotiable). \n8) After confirmation the office arranges a Pre-Placement Talk. \n9) The company conducts its selection and shortlists students for the interview. \n10) The results are announced usually on the same day. \n11) Students who receive confirmation letters are not allowed to appear before any other visiting company. \n12) Once into the selection process, no candidate can drop out at an intermediate stage. \n\nThe Training & Placement Cell, provides all audio visual facilities for PowerPoint Presentations, written test, group discussion and interviews. It plays\na very important and key role in counseling and guiding the students of the Collge for their successful career placement which is a crucial interface\nbetween the stages of completion of academic program of the students and their entry into the suitable employment. This Cell also coordinates various \nactivities related to the career of the students along with the industrial training. Recognizing the complexity of the career planning process and the\nmyriad of options available to graduates, the Department of Training and Placement conducts programmes that offer various services to meet the professional\ndevelopment needs of students. \n\nHaving an exposure to a good work culture in the beginning of their professional life guarantees success in all their endeavours. We have seen over the years\nthat the students trained in this institute are very well prepared to handle responsibilities and work with the most cutting-edge technology in the industry.\nThis belief works as a driving force for us to try and ensure that our students get a jump start in their career. We,at Training and Placement cell, provide\nour students with the best avenues to utilize their skills by helping them find gainful employment with the best of the engineering firms. \n\nFor placement a large number of prospective employers are contacted during the year and the number of companies visiting regularly this Institute are \nincreasing every year. \n\nThe objective of the T&P Cell is to look for a 100% employment of all the students therefore it follows policy of ' One Person One Job '. A candidate select\n-ed for one job is further restricted to other recruitment. \n \n\n                                                                        -X-X-X-\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n");
